				\begin{document}$${\varvec{C}}{\varvec{R}}=\frac{{\varvec{C}}{\varvec{I}}}{{\varvec{R}}{\varvec{I}}}$$\end{document}CR=CIRI, where R.I. is the random consistency index identified and assigned values by Saaty (1977; Saaty and Vargas 2012), as shown in Table 2. The consistent comparison is accepted if the CR has a value less than 0.1. If it exceeds, the matrix table is reconsidered until it gets less than 0.1Table 2
